<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8497] Merge index does not mark the Directories it creates as &apos;done&apos; and they are retained in the Directory cache.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8497</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After a Merge Indexes, the input directories on HDFS do not get closed (only released by the CachingDirectoryFactory). This causes the HDFSLocalityReporter to continue monitoring the input directories even after they are cleaned up/deleted. This results in a large volume of logged warnings on the Solr node.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Cloudera Search (CDH 5.4.5 Solr 4.10.3)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12928085">SOLR-8497</key>
            <summary>Merge index does not mark the Directories it creates as &apos;done&apos; and they are retained in the Directory cache.</summary>
